[14:02:21     4] - Continue the `printbuffer` migration in `rust/src/cJSON.rs`. Replace raw output storage with safe owned (`Vec<u8>`) and borrowed (`&mut [u8]`) representations, migrating the related printing helpers together. Keep C-allocation conversion at the exported FFI boundary so returned print buffers retain their current ownership contract.
[14:02:21     4] 
[14:02:21     4] ## Notes
[14:02:21     4] 
[14:02:21     4] - `printbuffer` spans `ensure`, `update_offset`, all `print_*` helpers, and all three print entry-point variants; do the conversion as one coordinated change so output offsets and NUL termination remain correct.
[14:02:21     4] - The safe-output rewrite must preserve the current behavior where some serializer branches write a NUL terminator without advancing `offset`; a writer abstraction should make its logical length explicit instead of retaining `update_offset`.
[14:02:21     4] - The current `cJSON` node graph still exposes raw links, so output-storage migration can be done independently but will not by itself make serializer traversal safe.
[14:02:21     4] - `cargo check-unsafe2` rejects new raw-pointer fields, including `AtomicPtr`; represent shared stored addresses with `AtomicUsize` and perform any address-to-pointer conversion only at the exported FFI boundary.
[14:02:21     4] - Existing warnings about `raw_ref_op` and function-pointer comparisons predate this cleanup.
